Pour water into mixing bowl and stir in brown sugar & salt.  Dump in flours and sprinkle yeast on top.  Mix on low speed until in-
corporated (possibly may need to add water as dough tends toward the dry), then switch to 2nd speed and knead for 8-10 min.
Cover and let rise until doubled.  Divide into 3-oz (or whatever size desired, but recipe yield is for 3-oz rolls) portions, roll and
place on lined sheet pans.  Place in cabinet to rise.  When ready to bake, score rolls once  and spray with water.  Bake at 325°
for 15 minutes, rotate & pull out vent, then bake another 5 minutes.
